## Test Specification

### `tests/unit/test_iteration.py`

```
Tier assignment from attempt_number
- attempt 1 → "targeted"
- attempt 3 → "targeted"
- attempt 4 → "full_rewrite"
- attempt 5 → "full_rewrite"
- attempt 6 → "brief_revision"
- attempt 7 → "abandon"
- attempt 10 → "abandon"

Oscillation detection
- weakest_dims = [cta, emotional_resonance, cta] → detected=True
- weakest_dims = [cta, cta, cta] → detected=False (not two alternating)
- weakest_dims = [cta, emotional_resonance, brand_voice] → detected=False
- only 2 attempts → never detected (insufficient history)
- oscillation detected → next tier is "full_rewrite" regardless of attempt_number

Regression detection (REGRESSION_THRESHOLD = 0.5)
- dimension drops 0.6 points → appears in dimensions_regressed
- dimension drops exactly 0.5 points → does NOT appear (boundary is exclusive)
- dimension drops 0.4 points → does NOT appear
- dimension improves → does NOT appear
- two regressions in same attempt → both appear in list

Strategy selection per dimension
- weakest="clarity"             → approach=FULL_REWRITE
- weakest="cta"                 → approach=TARGETED
- weakest="emotional_resonance" → approach=HOOK_REWRITE
- weakest="brand_voice"         → approach=TONE_REWRITE
- weakest="value_proposition"   → approach=TARGETED

Quality ratchet (V1 stub behavior)
- ratchet.update() does NOT change current_threshold in V1
- ratchet.update() logs "would_trigger" event when condition is met
- last 10 ads avg=8.0, threshold=7.0 → condition met (8.0 >= 7.0 + 0.5)
- last 10 ads avg=7.4, threshold=7.0 → condition NOT met (7.4 < 7.0 + 0.5)
- fewer than 10 ads in window → condition never met (insufficient data)
```

### `tests/unit/test_batch_runner.py`

```
Checkpointing
- completed brief_id saved after each ad
- resumed batch with 3 completed briefs skips those 3 brief_ids
- new run_id starts fresh even if brief_ids were completed in another run

Failure isolation
- exception during brief → logged as "failed", batch continues
- failed brief does not affect subsequent briefs
- batch_result.failed includes the failed brief_id

Batch result counts
- published + abandoned + failed == total briefs processed
```
